<div id="review_3800007829" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3800007829" />
    <a title="James W" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7044044-james-w"><img alt="James W" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615843324p2/7044044.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3800007829?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James W" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James W" href="/user/show/7044044-james-w">James W</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3800007829" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3729504286102607574">‘Happiness Power: How to Unleash Your Power and Lead a More Joyful Life,’ by author Robert Gill Jr., offers readers a comprehensive guide to defining (and finding) that ever so elusive concept of happiness.<br/><br/>Drawing upon his many years of personal and professional experience, Gill, a self-proclaimed ‘joyful optimist,’ offers readers a step-by-step guide to obtaining a more positive outlook on the life they currently have. Throughout the book, he tackles the ‘secret to happiness,’ detailing tips an</span>
  <span id="freeText3729504286102607574" style="display:none">‘Happiness Power: How to Unleash Your Power and Lead a More Joyful Life,’ by author Robert Gill Jr., offers readers a comprehensive guide to defining (and finding) that ever so elusive concept of happiness.<br /><br />Drawing upon his many years of personal and professional experience, Gill, a self-proclaimed ‘joyful optimist,’ offers readers a step-by-step guide to obtaining a more positive outlook on the life they currently have. Throughout the book, he tackles the ‘secret to happiness,’ detailing tips and ‘effortless mindfulness tricks,’ that is, strategies devised to help guide us through the day-to-day malaise of modern living. Additionally, Gill includes an appendix and chapter summaries (I wish more authors would do this!) that make for frustration-free future reference.<br /><br />While there’s a bevy of quotes, cited studies, thoughtful advice, and some pretty remarkable takeaways, Gill refuses to beat readers over the head, opting for a conversational tone that feels less like a self-help guru and more like a long-lost friend. But what really sets Gill’s book apart from the rest is the manner in which he wraps each and every sentence with a warm, optimistic tone. Regardless of your takeaway, I would have a hard time imagining anyone reading this and not feeling at least a little bit better about being alive.<br /><br />If you are anything like me, then you probably struggle to remain ‘in the moment.’ Thankfully, Robert Gill’s ‘Happiness Power’ provided me with a roadmap for stopping to smell those proverbial roses.<br /><br />Make no mistake, regardless of the gimmicky title and stock cover art—this is not just another run-of-the-mill ‘self-help’ book—it just might be the best ‘self-help’ book I’ve ever read_highly recommended!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3729504286102607574" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


