  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3764342246" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3764342246" />
    <a title="Grady" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1362506-grady"><img alt="Grady" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442472304p2/1362506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3764342246?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grady" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grady" href="/user/show/1362506-grady">Grady</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3764342246" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16260201186784187366">‘a deep connection between optimism and happiness because optimism reflects hope’<br/><br/>New Jersey author Robert Gill, Jr. publishes ArtMolds Journal, reflecting his love of art and sculpture, and has published the Long Island House Buyer’s Guide, reflecting his career as an investor in commercial and residential properties, adding to that category his book 90 DAYS TO YOUR FIRST REAL ESTATE INVESTMENT PURCHASE. His non-fiction books and articles on teaching, cooking, personal finance and more round out</span>
  <span id="freeText16260201186784187366" style="display:none">‘a deep connection between optimism and happiness because optimism reflects hope’<br /><br />New Jersey author Robert Gill, Jr. publishes ArtMolds Journal, reflecting his love of art and sculpture, and has published the Long Island House Buyer’s Guide, reflecting his career as an investor in commercial and residential properties, adding to that category his book 90 DAYS TO YOUR FIRST REAL ESTATE INVESTMENT PURCHASE. His non-fiction books and articles on teaching, cooking, personal finance and more round out his publications, to which he now adds HAPPINESS POWER.<br /><br />The author’s irresistibly joyous manner of writing makes this book addictive. If ever there were a time to share his outlook and insight and recommendations for living a life o happiness and joy, that time is NOW! And the fact that he teaches us that reaching that goal of happiness is completely within our own power to achieve produces a coaching guide that deserves wide dissemination for all readers.<br /><br />A hint of the quality of Gill’s book is evident in the opening of his Preface: ‘A young friend of the Nobel laureate, Bertrand Russell, once found the philosopher in a state of profound contemplation. “Why so meditative?” asked the young man. “Because I’ve made an odd discovery,” replied Russell. “Every time I talk to an intellectual, I feel quite certain that happiness is no longer a possibility. Yet when I talk with my gardener, I’m convinced of the opposite.” What a profound sentiment – is happiness truly tied to intellect? Is ignorance, indeed, bliss? Bertrand Russell found himself in a bit of a predicament as he weighed that sentiment heavily, and who can blame him? Happiness is as complex and profound as humans themselves, and it can be hard to grapple with for many. HAPPINESS POWER is a unique book that details how happiness’s life-satisfying emotion provides significant benefits to those who experience it.’ <br /><br />This spirit of sharing concepts and ideas of great thinkers as well as scientific studies on the impact of happiness and its source makes this book radiate the possibilities of securing that powerful state of mind. A glance at his chapter titles surveys the scope of the book - The Power of Happiness, Happiness and Physical Health, You Mental Health, The Power of Gratitude, The Power of Self-Kindness, The Power of Purpose, The Power of Family, Friends and Community, and The Power of Giving. <br /><br />Rich in takeaway thoughts, such as ‘Happiness does not depend on what we have; it depends on how we feel about what we have,’ and ‘Happiness is indeed a powerful emotion. Numerous studies have shown that happiness boosts motivation, creativity, and energy, It improves productivity,’ can be found on every page. The presentation is clear and accessible and rich in supportive advice – just the sort of book we all need to absorb. Very highly recommended. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16260201186784187366" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

