<div id="review_3802831274" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3802831274" />
    <a title="Elaine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70867093-elaine"><img alt="Elaine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618448366p2/70867093.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3802831274?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elaine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elaine" href="/user/show/70867093-elaine">Elaine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3802831274" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5340376023096987255">In this personal development book, the author gives readers a comprehensive guide to what is happiness and how to find it. Do you have everything you need, but still feel like something’s missing? This book will delve into your life and make you understand what real happiness can be. This is reflective of the unhappiness that exists in our society which continues to decline. Does social media or the endless pursuit of more wealth have anything to do with this? The author explores this deeply and</span>
  <span id="freeText5340376023096987255" style="display:none">In this personal development book, the author gives readers a comprehensive guide to what is happiness and how to find it. Do you have everything you need, but still feel like something’s missing? This book will delve into your life and make you understand what real happiness can be. This is reflective of the unhappiness that exists in our society which continues to decline. Does social media or the endless pursuit of more wealth have anything to do with this? The author explores this deeply and has you thinking clearly about different aspects of your life. He asks are you a TIgger or an Eeyore? Comparing these two well-known characters makes you think into the depth of your being and perhaps understand what really makes you tick. Research shows that most of our temperament tends to lean towards positivity or negativity. This is genetically predetermined and not really understood. In the appendix he includes a detailed list of words that express happiness which I found quite interesting. You finish this book thinking that even though happiness is not the end of all things, it doesn’t hurt to go through life happy.<br /></span>
