  <span id="freeText3243251216425551513" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book as an addition to the meditation and mindfulness that I have been working on and reading about recently. This book is nicely organized and starts with definitions of what happiness is, how to achieve it or at least improve it in out lives, and how to be more positive. As a person who tends toward skepticism, I appreciate that the book does not try to say that happiness is easy, but is a work in progress throughout our lives. I try each day, as the book suggests, to think of something positive even if my situation or day did not go as planned. There is always something to be thankful for.<br /><br />I received a free copy of this book via Booksprout and am voluntarily leaving a review.</span>
