<div id="review_3879942282" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3879942282" />
    <a title="Guadalupe Herrera" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/129001463-guadalupe-herrera"><img alt="Guadalupe Herrera" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611638666p2/129001463.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3879942282?book_show_action=true">Mar 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Guadalupe Herrera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Guadalupe Herrera" href="/user/show/129001463-guadalupe-herrera">Guadalupe Herrera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3879942282" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer936751162676756056"><strong>Wonderful Advice</strong><br/><br/>Robert Gill Jr., gives a wonderful outlook on happiness and what it can do for us as a person. One of the things he mentions is that we have the ability to make ourselves happy; it is not something that only comes from the outside. Even if, genetically, we are disposed to think in one direction or another (positively or negatively), we can essentially manifest our own happiness. I can appreciate what he states in his book as I have asked those I know if they can be happy on their</span>
  <span id="freeText936751162676756056" style="display:none"><strong>Wonderful Advice</strong><br /><br />Robert Gill Jr., gives a wonderful outlook on happiness and what it can do for us as a person. One of the things he mentions is that we have the ability to make ourselves happy; it is not something that only comes from the outside. Even if, genetically, we are disposed to think in one direction or another (positively or negatively), we can essentially manifest our own happiness. I can appreciate what he states in his book as I have asked those I know if they can be happy on their own through their own means. With mixed responses, it is evident that some of us let the negativity around us drown out the good that we have. I would recommend this book to anyone, but especially TO those who feel unworthy or if they feel as if they are not deserving of love or happiness.</span>
  <a data-text-id="936751162676756056" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


