        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3879962527" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15461947833322894124">Before reading this book, I thought that its background message would be “be happy with what you have”, the traditional self-help advice, but it is definitively much more than that. “Happiness Power” by author Robert Gill Jr turned me into an empowered person. I learned a lot about the advantages I already have: my physical and mental health, my work, my people (family, friends, and community) and all the power I can unleash through gratitude, self-kindness, giving to others and much more. This </span>
  <span id="freeText15461947833322894124" style="display:none">Before reading this book, I thought that its background message would be “be happy with what you have”, the traditional self-help advice, but it is definitively much more than that. “Happiness Power” by author Robert Gill Jr turned me into an empowered person. I learned a lot about the advantages I already have: my physical and mental health, my work, my people (family, friends, and community) and all the power I can unleash through gratitude, self-kindness, giving to others and much more. This was an informative, enlightening and thought provoking read, assisting me in discovering my purpose in life! <br /><br />Moreover, through this book, I learned about the Happiness Science, a new and empirical field of social science known as positive psychology, which is really interesting for me. I will surely keep on reading about this! </span>
  <a data-text-id="15461947833322894124" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

